This article first appeared at southern weekend and is not to be reprinted without permission

Wen | southern weekend reporters Jing Yibu, Li Zailei, Wang Weikai

Southern weekend intern, Gong Roushan, Ye Zi

Editor in chief | Zhang Yue

From New Year's Eve to the first day of the Lunar New Year, many hospitals in Wuhan are still running short of supplies.

Southern weekend contacted six Wuhan hospitals and was told there was still a big gap in medical supplies, mainly disposable materials, protective clothing, masks, goggles and so on.

"The gap is measured in tens of thousands of units, " Mr. Chang of Hankou Hospital in Wuhan told southern weekend. The hospital's Daily consumption of protective clothing is between 500 and 800 units, and at the current rate of consumption, "it can last about three days. ".

On the one hand is the material emergency, on the other hand is the social rescue force surge.

Since January 23,2020, nine Wuhan hospitals have announced their acceptance of charitable donations, and many of the calls in the announcements have been busy for several days.

At both ends of the supply and demand chain stuck logistics.

On New Year's Eve, a Yunda express related official told southern weekend that he had not yet received a notice from the government to coordinate the delivery of medical supplies by express delivery companies. "Wuhan's cars can't get out, and basically they can't get in, " he said. "going in requires coordination. ".

On the first night of the New Year, they were organized. Cainiao United 13 logistics enterprises at home and abroad, including Zhongtong, Shentong, Yunda, AirCity international logistics group, Xinke Logistics, etc. , to open a green channel for the free transportation of donated relief materials to the society in Wuhan, at present, the first batch of 100,000 masks have been transported from Anhui to Wuhan.

1
Saved from the hospital

1

###Saved from the hospital

January 24 is the New Year's Eve, Wuhan Guanggu Software Park downstairs almost everyone wearing masks, only a pair of eyes, walking, a few meters away from each other.

"It's already been a round, " said a cashier at a convenience store on Chongren road in Hankou. Delivery trucks were stopped outside the city, and the store was still waiting to be notified if it was open.

Things are even more tense at the hospital. On Jan. 22, Chen Xia, a doctor at the Wuhan Union Hospital, told southern weekly that the hospital had a limited number of masks to hand out to non front line departments, where each doctor was given only a few. "The hospital mainly uses the material in the front line, the fever ward, the Department of aspiration, the Department of infection and so on. "

Although the instructions say a mask can last 6-8 hours, it is recommended to replace it in 2-3 hours, and Chen regrets not stocking up on masks at his local pharmacy. On New Year's Eve, she received good news -- a friend of a friend was in Cambodia, and a handful of surgical masks were on sale at the local pharmacy for $3 A box. Chen Xia Li Matuo people bought four boxes a total of 200 masks.

Xu Xiaoning, a doctor at Hanyang Hospital in Wuhan, told southern weekend that as of January 23, the hospital had about 1,350 suits in stock and in use. The hospital has more than 1,000 medical staff on duty every day, according to the normal supply of materials, each medical staff need two sets of protective clothing, one for normal use, the other for damaged reserve. But the actual supply is not enough.

Due to the shortage of protective clothing, the hospital can only provide fever ward, infectious ward, Respiratory Ward and other key areas of health care personnel a suit of protective clothing, and repeated use requirements. This is already a good condition, because "other general ward and ICU ward did not send" .

Stocks of medical-grade masks, hats, gloves and shoe covers are even scarcer. On January 23, Xu Xiaoning told the southern weekend reporter, "N95 mask none, now are using ordinary masks, wearing is better than not wearing. ". If not restocked in time, these ordinary masks will be used up in about three days.

Hanyang hospitals began to openly solicit medical and nursing resources from the public on the 23rd. As of the evening of the 24th, more than 200 masks and 800 pairs of gloves had been collected, but protective clothing was still missing.

"normally the N95 mask is changed every four hours. We will put a normal mask inside the N95 mask, so only the ordinary mask will be changed, and the N95 mask will last longer, " Wan of the Wuhan Hospital of Traditional Chinese Medicine told southern weekend.

Earlier on January 20, Wuhan Health Commission established a new pneumonia prevention and control headquarters, the headquarters of the unified allocation of medical resources.

Mr. Wan told the southern weekend reporter that he had to report to the headquarters three times a day at 8:00,14:00 and 18:00, respectively. The contents of the report were the hospital's inventory, demand, consumption, etc. . After the headquarters was informed of the specific conditions of each hospital, and then combined with the inventory for the distribution of health care resources.

2
Pick it up at the border

2

###Pick it up at the border

On New Year's Eve, there were few masks left for some of the journalists working continuously in Wuhan. They received masks from volunteers on the first day of the Lunar New Year, but protective clothing and goggles and other equipment could not be obtained due to traffic restrictions.

"It's very difficult to move around the city. Volunteers tried to send me some pairs of glasses, but they couldn't, " said a reporter in Wuhan, "On the first afternoon of the Lunar New Year, taxis can still be found in the city, but not across districts. After midnight, there will be a general ban on motor vehicles. "

It is not only restricted to all districts in Wuhan, but also very difficult for vehicles outside the city to get in. Originally pulled the truck driver also have a fear of difficulties, "fear of going in (Wuhan) will not come out. ".

Several people in Wuhan told southern weekend that there was a serious lag in logistics. Xu Xiaoning told southern weekend that the delivery speed was limited and could not reach Han for a short time. Some couriers were stranded at the Wuhan border and could not enter the city. "The hospital needs to send people from the limited staff to the border to hand over, " he said.

To avoid further spread of the disease, from 10:00 on January 23, Wuhan city-wide bus, subway, ferry, long-distance passenger transport suspended operations; airport, Railway Station from the Han Channel temporarily closed. Wuhan "closed" , medical resources to reach the front line is even more difficult.

At this time, a number of people living in Wuhan organized themselves, through the establishment of Wechat group to pass on material information, to seek support for the hospital, the source of goods and truck drivers, to build a self-help transport network.

Zheng Quan, a native of Wuhan, runs a transportation company and has his own fleet of vehicles. They have joined the volunteer transport team. January 22, a total of about 50,000 masks from Shandong to be shipped to Wuhan, there are 70% of the cargo did not arrive, Wuhan "closed" .

Zheng Quan received information, let the other side of the goods sent to Xiangyang, and then sent the convoy did not go home for the New Year driver to meet the Wuhan border. New Year's Eve, the overnight transfer of goods in, and then distributed to the major pharmacies in Wuhan. On the first morning of the New Year's Day, all the goods are divided up.

"Some of the masks were given to street cleaners and traffic police without compensation, " Zheng said.

Zheng Quan told southern weekend that there is a shortage of human resources. Even if the company has its own fleet, there are only two or three drivers left, and the actual number of vehicles that can be transported is only two or three. In addition to the Information asymmetry, many needy citizens or medical institutions can not reach him, fleet resources have not been effectively used.

Even so, Zheng Quan's motorcade will soon be unable to assist in the distribution of medical resources in Wuhan. According to a notice issued by the Wuhan new pneumonia prevention and Control Headquarters on the afternoon of January 25, from 00:00 on the 26th, the central city area will be closed to vehicular traffic except for licensed transportation vehicles, free transportation vehicles and official vehicles.

"If the government asks us to do something, we will do it, " Zheng said. He hoped that the delivery of medical supplies could be concentrated in one or two large logistics companies that could meet the capacity requirements, unified receipt and distribution of assistance at designated locations to reduce confusion and ensure the orderly and timely delivery of materials.

3
Self-organized truckers

3

###Self-organized truckers

In a wechat group of nearly 500 people, volunteers updated the news 24 hours a day after the city was shut down, this includes asking the public to help transport aid resources, the distribution list of community taxis after the shutdown of motor vehicles, and the demand for materials in various hospitals.

Cao, 34, was the driver who transported the mask back to Wuhan. He was from Hunan Province and did not return home for the Lunar New Year because of fears of becoming a carrier of the virus and spreading it to his family. On New Year's Eve, he drove a seven-seater van with 75 boxes of N95 masks, each containing about 304 masks. On the first day of the New Year at two o'clock in the morning, he just finished the day of transport work.

At first, Cao said, he planned to take the Tianhe Airport Expressway, but the other party would not let him through. After he made it clear that he was an employee of a logistics company and needed to go to Xiangyang to transfer medical supplies, the other side still insists that must have a health certificate issued by the hospital in order to pass.

He then took the national highway and was able to leave the city after his temperature was normal. "Now you have to take your temperature on the way out of Wuhan, and you have to stop every 30 or 40 kilometers along the national highway to take your temperature, " Cao said. As a first-line freight driver in direct contact with medical resources, he has to wash his hands every day, put on several layers of protective masks, take temperature regularly, "this is responsible for others. ".

When loading supplies into Wuhan, such as face masks, the truckers are required to register their vehicles first. If there is no abnormality in body temperature, the checkpoint staff will issue an immunity pass and the driver's pass to enter the city.

Li Ming is the boss of Sichuan Yuanbang Logistics Company. In the past two days, he has posted information on his friend circle and WECHAT group. If there are medical tools such as masks and daily necessities to be transported to Hubei, his motorcade can help transport them free of charge, the van leaves from Leshan and Chengdu.

He delivered supplies to disaster areas during the 2008 earthquake in Wenchuan County. He told southern weekend reporters that if there is a material donation, must first contact the Hubei side, otherwise it is difficult to send in. On douyin, there are some trucks carrying goods to Hubei Province, many of which are marked with "goods transportation" banners, but according to Chen Ming, these banners are not enough. You also need to get a pass from the government.

"If you have supplies, contact the government first, then report the vehicle information, then load the vehicle and go, " Li told southern weekend.

Chen Peng is an anonymous Heilongjiang van driver, his normal business is to deliver goods to all parts of the country, a few days ago to Wuhan delivery, just caught up with Fengcheng, he chose to stay. On New Year's Eve, he reported his van and phone messages to the Wuhan Red Cross, ready for dispatch.

"The epidemic is so serious, and I am in Wuhan, do not go out to make trouble for everyone. " In the telephone, Chen Peng's voice sounded very optimistic, bright, from time to time politely laughed. When asked for his name, he smiled in a north eastern accent and said, just write down a nice driver from Heilongjiang.

He told southern weekend that after he decided not to leave the city, he bought a large quantity of instant noodles, bread, dumplings, Yuanxiao and other living materials, as well as some masks, which would last him about 10 days. He regretted, however, that no one had called him to help with the delivery of supplies.

4
Plane, train, automobile constitute the green channel of logistics

4

###Plane, train, automobile constitute the green channel of logistics

Among Logistics Companies, SF express and Jd.com were the first to organize a special rescue route to Wuhan. SF deploys planes, jd.com deploys cars and trains.

At 14:30 on January 24, a Shunfeng air plane carrying 16 tons of medical supplies landed safely at Wuhan Tianhe Airport. This was the second relief plane to deliver medical supplies to Wuhan on the same day. The first plane arrived at 1205 hours. The two special planes brought 32 tons of medicine and masks.

The day before, SF express announced that the company will make every effort to coordinate resources, priority to ensure the delivery of special needs materials to Wuhan Transportation Services.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, SF & F reissued a notice to advise domestic individuals to contact local charitable organizations to coordinate donations for the delivery of relief materials to Wuhan and other places at home and abroad Overseas donations first contact a qualified community groups or foundations, receive confirmation, SF express can provide domestic public transport support.

On the same day, JD.com logistics also officially opened a special channel for all parts of the country to come to the aid of Wuhan, accepting requests for assistance from local governments, public welfare organizations, enterprises and institutions, medical device manufacturers and other organizations, individual donations are not accepted.

People in Jd.com told southern weekend that by the 15th day of the 1st Lunar month, Jd.com logistics will give priority to the delivery of orders designated by medical institutions.

At 10 pm on January 21, a drug factory in Yichang, Hubei Province, called for help. The 800 boxes of 16,000 boxes of Oseltamivir phosphate granules needed to be urgently delivered, he said. JD.com deployed two 7.6-meter-long logistics vehicles overnight, to deliver these medicines in a timely manner.

In the case of "closure" , JD.com logistics applied for an emergency transfer order, in close coordination with China Railway Express, through the anti-epidemic high-speed rail green channel to transport anti-epidemic materials.

On New Year's Eve, epidemic prevention supplies from Beijing and Guangzhou to Wuhan were shipped on the G521 high-speed railway from Beijing West to Hankou and K1080 baggage cars from Guangzhou north to Wuchang. In addition to the epidemic-prevention supplies purchased by Wuhan residents from JD.com, a batch of epidemic-prevention supplies donated by caring enterprises was loaded on both trains, they include 10,000 face masks, 1,000 chemical suits, 7,200 bottles of hand sanitizer, 7,200 bottles of detergent and 40 air purifier.

On the evening of January 25, Cainiao announced that 13 logistics enterprises, including Zhongtong, Shentong, Yunda and AirCity international logistics group, have opened a green channel for the free transportation of relief materials donated by the society in Wuhan.

But in fact, the current express time limit is still not easy to guarantee.

The resistance comes from three aspects: the constant weather effect of rain in Wuhan; the tight freight resources during the Spring Festival; and the delay of the local traffic epidemic prevention.

A person from SF said to southern weekend reporters that the recent rain in Wuhan, logistics transport time extension, "can not run up the car. ". Moreover, during the Spring Festival, the staff all went home, the resources are not sufficient, in this regard, Shunfeng took out 150 million Yuan Special Incentive Fund, reward the staff on duty during the Spring Festival.

In traffic control, "we now all express delivery to and from Wuhan, even if it is transit, must strictly in accordance with national regulations, in transit site for secondary disinfection, " which inevitably extended the time limit for logistics.

On January 25, a Wuhan resident told southern weekend that he had seen a large number of military vehicles escorting supplies roaring through the streets of Wuhan. The "regulars" are about to enter.

(at the request of the interviewees, Chen Xia, Xu Xiaoning, Li Ming and Chen Peng were assumed names. Southern weekend reporters Huang Jinping and Xu Tingfang contributed to this report.)
